SUMMARY:Polk Street Pollinator Planting (Charlotte)
DESCRIPTION:Join NCWF Charlotte Wildlife Stewards Chapter and the city Tree Canopy Preservation Program to help create pollinator habitat along the Urban Arboretum Trail in Charlotte’s Greenville neighborhood. Pocket gardens are a great way to support pollinators and other wildlife by installing native plants. Volunteers will install hundreds of pollinator plugs and small containerized plants during this fun work day! \nPlease bring your favorite pair of gardening gloves. Tools will be provided but feel free to bring your own trowel! \nREGISTER HERE
URL:https://ncwf.org/event/polk-street-pollinator-planting-charlotte/
CATEGORIES:Featured
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://ncwf.org/wp-content/uploads/PollinatorPlantingUAT.jpg
END:VEVENT
